==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Canaster
<hw>Ca*nas"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>canasta</ets>, <ets>canastro</ets>, basket, fr. L.
<ets>canistrum</ets>. See <er>Canister</er>.]</ety> <def>A kind of
tobacco for smoking, made of the dried leaves, coarsely broken; -- so
called from the rush baskets in which it is packed in South
America.</def> <rj><au>McElrath.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

